init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The story follows the adventures of the United States in their quest to find out what happened to the rest of the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The US government is in a state of chaos.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The son was a ruthless dictator.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He had the power to do whatever he wanted, and he did.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The people of the United States were desperate.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The leader responded by sending in the military to break up the protests.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The rest of the world was horrified.
